  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Efficacy of High Dose Vitamin C Therapy in Shock Patients</measure>
    <time_frame>30 days</time_frame>
    <description>Given the grim prognosis of septic and hypovolemic shock, we aim to study the efficacy on an alternative treatment modality by implementing high dose vitamin C therapy in our patient population. Through previous investigations, especially research in the burn patient population, we expect that high dose vitamin C therapy will be beneficial to patients with hypovolemic or septic shock.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
